FT  17 DEC 93 / Landlords to get VAT refunds
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HM Customs &amp; Excise is to refund value added tax levied when landlords pay
tenants to surrender commercial leases, following a defeat in the European
Court.
Customs said yesterday it would refund the VAT paid to all registered
traders from April 1 1989, when its practice was adopted.
