<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / Red tape on sick pay to be studied
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The government has agreed to examine how it can best reduce the red tape for
employers in the administration of the Statutory Sick Pay scheme, Lisa Wood
writes.
Business organisations including the Confederation of British Industry and
the Institute of Directors have expressed concern about the proposed cut in
statutory sick pay subsidy to employers. The bill passed through its Commons
stages on Wednesday.
In future large companies, which can now claim back 80 per cent of statutory
sick pay after six weeks of employee absence will not be able to do so.
Smaller companies which can claim 80 per cent after six weeks will be able
to claim 100 per cent after four weeks.
