</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The heroic tread of 20th century democracy shuffles a further pace forward
today, with the introduction of a Citizen's Charter for public toilets.
The Audit Commission is taking this great leap forward partly in response to
pressure from the likes of Jon Owen Jones, Labour MP for Cardiff central,
already and inevitably dubbed by some at Westminster as 'Spendapenny Jones'.
