FT  15 DEC 93 / International Capital Markets: Brazil puts 36 groups on list
for 1994 sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   RIO DE JANEIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Brazil has drawn up a list of 36 companies that could be privatised in 1994,
Reuter reports from Rio de Janeiro.
Mr Andre Franco Montoro Filho, president of the privatisation commission,
said the list included 19 companies in the petrochemicals sector.
Preliminary sale dates have been alloted to 32 companies which, according to
the commission, will be sold for around Dollars 5bn in total.
Cobra, the computer group and Arafertil, a fertiliser producer, are set for
sale in February. The sale of copper mining group Mineracao Caraiba,
aerospace group Embraer and shipping company Lloyd Brasileiro have been set
for March.
The list also includes regional electricity distributors Light and Escelsa
in June and July respectively.
