<HEADLINE>
FT  15 DEC 93 / International Company News: Great Eagle plans reorganisation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Great Eagle Holdings said it was considering reorganising its commercial and
office property development activities and spinning them off into a single
unit to be listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, Reuter reports from Hong
Kong.
Other units of Great Eagle will continue to be primarily involved in
investment in residential, industrial and retail properties and hotels.
The new commercial property unit will remain a subsidiary of Great Eagle
after the listing, the company said.
The stock exchange has not yet considered the proposals or application for
listing, the company said.
</TEXT>
