<HEADLINE>
FT  15 DEC 93 / International Company News: Federal Express delivers sharp
earnings rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEMPHIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Federal Express, the biggest overnight delivery company in the US, posted a
sharp rise in earnings to Dollars 59.7m, or Dollars 1.07 a share, during its
second quarter, up from Dollars 35.4m, or 65 cents, a year earlier, Reuter
reports from Memphis.
Earnings per share outstripped analysts' forecasts ranging from 90 cents to
Dollars 1. Revenues for the period ending November 30 climbed 8 per cent to
Dollars 2.12bn from Dollars 1.96bn, while operating income rose 33 per cent
to Dollars 149.7m from Dollars 112.7m.
International operating profit was Dollars 2.1m on revenues of Dollars
583.7m, while last year international operations lost Dollars 37.8m on
revenues of Dollars 564.3m. Domestic profit slipped to Dollars 147.6m from
Dollars 150.5m, despite a 10 per cent revenue gain to Dollars 1.54bn.
</TEXT>
