<HEADLINE>
FT  15 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Manakin proposes further distribution
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Manakin Holdings, the investment trust which went into voluntary liquidation
in 1991, had a net asset value of 82p per share at October 15, against 68p
six months earlier and 100p at the previous year-end.
Since the appointment of liquidators in October 1991 five distributions to
shareholders totalling Pounds 70.1m (342p per share) have been made. A
further repayment of 8p will be made on January 21.
The net loss for the year was Pounds 435,445, against a profit of Pounds
22,067. Losses per share were 2.1p (earnings 0.1p).
The liquidator said that it was likely that losses would continue to occur
as it was not his intention to invest funds for income purposes, but to
distribute funds to shareholders as soon as possible.
He expected the liquidation to take another two years to complete.
</TEXT>
